Van Mander mentions a Temptation of Christ waer [=daer] men van boven...[sic] The conception of a mountainous landscape with a view down from the mountains which are so high that clouds in [onleesbaar] then in Paulus... column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] 76. For catalogue of lost pictures by Bruegel: The Temptation of Christ. Van Mander mentions a Temptation of Christ waer [=daer] men van boven...[sic] The conception of a mountainous landscape with a view down from the mountains which are so high that clouds in [onleesbaar] then in Paulus... Drawing in Louvre. T. [= Tolnay] has drawn attention a painting (fig. 152) in; [verso] an Amsterdam private collection of a Temptation of Christ with a vast mountainous landscape and Christ quite [onleesbaar] by Lucas van Valckenborch. The height with the clouds and the [onleesbaar] trees almost literally reproduced from the Paulus seem suggest fact that a Moses on Mount Sinai by T. Verhaecht in the coll. of F. Lugt, the Hague, may be closer to the lost Temptation. Das Bild schon bei Glück, N° 49 herausgegeben.</content>
